                     <interp inst="t18000528-117-person1148" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a constable, I received this spoon from Mr. Shepherd, (produces it;) the prisoner said, d-n my eyes if that is not my spoon now.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I found the spoon, at the corner of Portland-street.</p>
               <p>Morris. This is Mr. Middleton's crest; I counted over the spoons and found one short of the number, I have brought the fellow to it. (Produces it.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner called his serjeant, who gave him a good character. <rs id="t18000528-117-verdict674" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18000528-117-verdict674" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs> (Aged 21.)</p>
